attributes.description: Name of this profile, usually based on the publisher it pertains to e.g. "openEHR", "cdisc", etc.
attributes.name: profile_name

attributes.description: Allowed type substitutions: Actual RM type names keyed by AOM built-in types which can substitute for them in an archetype. E.g. `<key = "ISO8601_DATE", value = "String">` means that if RM property `TYPE._some_property_` is of type `String`, an `ISO8601_DATE` is allowed at that position in the archetype.
attributes.name: aom_rm_type_substitutions

attributes.description: List of mappings of lifecycle state names used in archetypes to AOM lifecycle state names:
attributes.name: aom_lifecycle_mappings

attributes.description: Mappings from AOM built-in types to actual types in RM: whenever the type name is encountered in an archetype, it is mapped to a specific RM type.
attributes.name: aom_rm_type_mappings

attributes.description: Equivalences of RM primitive types to in-built set of primitive types. Used to determine which AOM `C_PRIMITIVE_OBJECT` descendant is used for a primitive type. Typical entries:
attributes.name: rm_primitive_type_equivalences

meta_info.description: Profile of common settings relating to use of reference model(s) and terminology for a given archetype developing organisation.
meta_info.name: AOM_PROFILE
